{"lemma":"عَلَفُ","slug":"عَلَفُ","root":"ع.ل.ف","root_slug":"ع-ل-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ل-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n30254","n30255","n30265"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fodder, provender, grass, hay"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"edible seeds or fruits of an acacia","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"umbrella thorn acacia (Vachellia tortilis)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to feed (an animal), to fodder"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to give abundant fodder, to feed"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grow pods (said of an acacia)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"The noun عَلَف (ʕalaf, “fodder”) is the most-frequent word of this root and, apparently its singular origin, hails from a form within the root ء ل ف (ʔ l f) such as أَلِفَ (ʔalifa, “to start to like said about animals near their nourishment”) etc. as quoted there."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30254","headword_ar":"عِلْفٌ","root":"Elf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A great eater;"},{"kind":"text","text":"one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who eats much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, O, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEotalafN","text_ar":"مُعْتَلَفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[perhaps a mistranscription for ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEotalifN","text_ar":"مُعْتَلِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", but see 8]. (TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajarapN","text_ar":"شَجَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of ElYemen, the leaves of which are like"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the grape"},{"kind":"text","text":"[-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vine"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they are pressed"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the nosebags of horses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the TA here inserting"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY AlmxAbY","text_ar":"فى المخابى"},{"kind":"text","text":", for which I read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY AlmaxaAliY","text_ar":"فى المَخَالِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and it is there added"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayusaw~aY","text_ar":"وَيُسَوَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", app. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and made into a flat mass,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and dried, and flesh-meat is cooked therewith instead of with vinegar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and they"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the leaves]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are used as a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DimaAd","text_ar":"ضِمَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dressing for wounds"},{"kind":"text","text":"] ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayuDam~adu bihi","text_ar":"وَيُضَمَّدُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (K accord. to the TA. [But in the place of these words, the CK and my MS. copy of the K have"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabiDam~K","text_ar":"وَبِضَمٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as relating to a form of the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaluwfapN","text_ar":"عَلُوفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", there mentioned in the next sentence.])"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30255","headword_ar":"عَلَفٌ","root":"Elf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is for beasts, or horses and the like; (S, O;) a word of well-known meaning; (K;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fodder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"provender for beasts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food of cattle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of animals,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of quadrupeds;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food with which the beast is fed"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEolaf","text_ar":"مِعْلَف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manger"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mgh:) accord. to ISh, applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"both"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$iy$N","text_ar":"حَشِيشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) said by ISd to be the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaDiym","text_ar":"قَضِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[generally meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barley"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the beast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in the present art.:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaluwfapN","text_ar":"عَلُوفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EilaAfN","text_ar":"عِلَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuluwfapN","text_ar":"عُلُوفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, O, K) and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolaAfN","text_ar":"اَعْلَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalafapN","text_ar":"عَلَفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo","text_ar":"هُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealafu Als~ilaAHi wajazaru Als~ibaAEi","text_ar":"عَلَفُ السِّلَاحِ وَجَزَرُ السِّبَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are the provender of the weapons, and the flesh that is food of the beasts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"birds, of prey"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Mgh","S","O","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n30265","headword_ar":"عُلَّفٌ","root":"Elf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloH","text_ar":"طَلْح"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which resembles the fresh bean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and upon which, when they come forth, the camels pasture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pods,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"receptacles of the fruit, thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TlH","text_ar":"طلح"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it succeeds the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baramap","text_ar":"بَرَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kidney-bean called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luwbiyaA='","text_ar":"لُوبِيَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar, TA:) the n. un. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~afapN","text_ar":"عُلَّفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) AHn says that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is like the great Syrian carob"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xar~uwabap","text_ar":"خَرُّوَبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xar~uwb","text_ar":"خَرُّوب"},{"kind":"text","text":"q. v.]),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except that it is bigger, and in it are grains like lupines, of a tawny colour, upon which the cattle pasturing at their pleasure feed, but which men eat not save in case of necessity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like thereof in size, of the fruit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":", is also termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~afN","text_ar":"عُلَّفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": what is smaller than it, like the fruit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salam","text_ar":"سَلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samur","text_ar":"سَمُر"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofuT","text_ar":"عُرْفُط"},{"kind":"text","text":", is [properly] termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hubolap","text_ar":"حُبْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~af","text_ar":"عُلَّف"},{"kind":"text","text":"are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long, and expanded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extended:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) [it is also said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~afN","text_ar":"عُلَّفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAk","text_ar":"اَرَاك"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 196.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA","IAar"]}]}}